public static class WorkflowTestSuite.WorkflowTest
extends AbstractXmlObject

A suite consists of one or more tests. The test defines the workflow definition to execute, the input variables, and the sequence of work item responses.

captureWorkflowLaunch

public void captureWorkflowLaunch(sailpoint.tools.xml.XMLReferenceResolver resolver,
                                  WorkflowLaunch src)
Capture the workflow launch state. This is what Workflower just call, setWorkflowLaunch is only used during XML parsing.

We must make a copy of this since we won't save capture state until the case has advanced and the WorkflowLaunch object will have been modified by then and contain things other than the initial launch arguments.

public WorkflowTestSuite.WorkItemResponse removeStubResponse(java.lang.String id)
Look for a stub response for a given work item id and remove it. It will normally be fleshed out with work item completion state and inserted back with addFinishedResponse.

addFinishedResponse

public void addFinishedResponse(WorkflowTestSuite.WorkItemResponse finished)
Insert a finished response into the list. This goes after the previously finished responses and before the stubs.

clearStubResponses

public void clearStubResponses()
Remove any stub responses that were created during capture. A stub response is defined as one with a non-null workItemId. Normally these are all at the end.
